latestPosts.caption:
This one was only possible because my mom insisted me for this while I was recovering. For the first time I doubted my potential and it felt as if I couldnt achieve this, only for her call to state " try once, this oppurtunity wont come back". 
The next 3 days post selection were all about hardcore practice session and coordination and constant rants over texts and voice notes to @maitri_solanki_ about how I was feeling and surviving the anxiety and stress. 
This was a team effort and it wont be possible without their support and management as well.

Posting this as the only entry to march, as this was the only good thing that happened in the last 30 days. 
Thankyou maa🧿
